metrics_conclusion: Vectors has higher complexity than the average song  in terms Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion:
Vectors is written in the key of F♯ Minor.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 7th most popular key among Minor keys and     the 15th most popular  among all keys. Minor keys, along with major keys, are a common choice for popular music.  The three most important chords, built off the 1st, 4th and 5th scale degrees are all minor chords (F♯ minor, B minor, and C♯ minor).

See the F♯ Minor Cheat Sheet for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: Some of this instrumental passage is repeated after the chorus as well. Once again, it's difficult to sync when everything is an 8th ahead of the beat. And the guitar transcription is from the official sheet music.
This one has really bad sync issues that I can't fix unfortunately. The A/C# chord is technically up to interpretation because both guitars and the bass play riffs there.

This is the last one I'll upload for tonight. I'll try to get back to Vectors for the verse (2), pre-chorus, and maybe the solo. It may be a while before I go back to Euphemia because I don't have the mp3 to analyze the backing synth chords in the verse.

Replaced the Euphemia intro with the real outro of Vectors. More to come. It was very difficult to sync this. Partially because of the chords all being an 8th note ahead of the beat. But also because the last D chord is technically a fermata. It's hard for me to tell if this was recorded to a click track or not since it ALMOST lines up with the number of measures I've given it here.
